data.description: SELLER SAYS SELL, SELL, SELL! Priced for quick sale. Sellers loss can be your gain with this Exquisite Equestrian zoned, Custom built home situated on 2.5 acres located in one of DeLand's most desirable areas! The back of the lot backs up to State preserve and riding trails that go as far as Orange City! Prepare to be wowed with all the features this home has to offer, from the open floor plan with trey ceilings to the well thought out lighting features coupled with the abundant natural lighting. The gourmet kitchen is a perfect place for entertaining with six burner gas stovetop is sure to impress any chef, built in double ovens, wine/beer fridge, a walk in pantry and lots of room for entertaining. The high output three sided fireplace is a great source of heat in the winter months and can be enjoyed from the living room, dining room and kitchen . The impressive master bedroom with his and her walk in closets features an equally impressive master bathroom with low maintenance oversized stone walk-in shower. Step through french doors to the covered and screened lanai perfect for enjoying your morning coffee and watching the wild life in the private back yard. The covered screened breeze way opens up to a host of options including the outdoor kitchen that looks over the pool and hot tub. Working on your tan poolside, watching the game on the tv, or entertaining friends has never been more stylish with the amazing screened pool with several patios and an outdoor kitchen! The main home is very large with two bedrooms and two bathrooms. There is also a spacious and charming two bedroom with one bathroom cabana guest suite just across the pool for in laws, family or guests. Above the 3 bay garage you'll find another oversized bonus room. Close proximity to I4, shopping, dining, and the downtown historic Deland Mainstreet.
